                    "company": "Dive Center Start-Up",
                    "description": "As director and share holder, I traveled the world to develop our DiveVersity Franchise concept. Worked hands on and as a trainer with our franchisees and staff. As director and shareholder I was responsible for maintaining and supporting 16 dive centers and over 50 staff members in 6 countries world wide. \n\nNext to working with existing shops I was responsible for the development and acquisition of new rental agreements with leading hotel chains and resort development companies. I worked with W Hotels for the middle east, acquired exclusive rights with Pierre et Vacance/Center Parcs in the Netherlands, Belgium and France and acquired exclusive rights with the Amari Hotel group in Bangkok for the DiveVersity franchise concept for their future hotels. \n\nCo-developed the franchise concept including international tax rulings, e-commerce rulings, loyalty programs, exclusive dive brand deals, implementation of a private label travel module, branding and buying deals for the franchisees. \n\nWorked on business deals and business relations in Sudan, Thailand, Egypt and Morocco. Unfortunately the global economic crisis, riots, natural disasters and the Arabic Spring forced me to down size the company back to basic and move back to Cura\u00e7ao in mid 2010",
